          "format": "image/jpeg",
          "description": "Small, square sheet of beige paper with images on each side. On one side are two parallel lines running the length of the page. Between the two lines is a wide graphite zig-zag scribble. On the other side, a version of Whistler\u2019s \u201cbutterfly\u201d signature occupies the whole page. An S-shaped blue watercolor line makes up the butterfly\u2019s body. Its wings are two crescent shapes, one painted light gray and the other unpainted, with fan-shaped peach areas at the outer edges.",
